### Conflicts
Reviewers, this pull request conflicts with the following ones:

* [#22867](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/22867) (test: Extend test coverage of BIP125 and document confusing/incon

concept ACK
successfully ran test with 
<details>
<summary> commenting test_rpc subtest </summary>

```
2021-09-21T10:20:52.294000Z TestFramework (INFO): Initializing test directory /tmp/bitcoin_func_test_gvoms1s4
2021-09-21T10:20:57.334000Z TestFramework (INFO): Running test simple doublespend...
2021-09-21T10:20:57.352000Z TestFramework (INFO): Running test doublespend chain...\
What happens if this output is removed? Previously the wallet would also "donate" the change to the fee.

IIUC what you mean: without this output, no new utxo to the internal MiniWallet scriptPubKey is created, i.e. we would probably run out of funds (or, could only create as many transactions as there are coinbase outputs from the pre-mined blocks from the test framework).
